Having arrived there, they did what was told them, and showed the people great friendship, enquiring diligently who were the most distinguished among them, upon whom they conferi-ed great honour, giving them many presents of small value, which however seemed in their eyes to be very pre- cious and costly: — yea, they awaited them with great re- joicing and shouting, falling down at the feet of the givers, seeing them dressed in such costly raiments, and not being accustomed to this they thought them Gods.
